<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-092-598  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 092 598.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  March 6 1989 v23 n9 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Abbott stems records overflow. (text retrieval system )</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cortese, Amy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Faced with the prospect of finding room for 500,000 3 x 5 indexcards in its increasingly crowded warehouse, Abbott Laboratorieshas begun a six-year project to bring the records into anautomated retrieval system.andP;  The system will be based on a WangLaboratories VS 100.andP;  About 140,000 of the index cards have beenentered into the Basis retrieval software on the VS 1000 withinthe first three months of the project.andP;  The laboratory has alreadyexperienced cost savings in project time.andP;  For instance, adestruction order process, which determines the viability ofdocuments, has been trimmed from two months to six hours.andP;  Theproject includes six databases on each document, indexed bycontents and location.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Abbott Laboratories (data processing).andO;Ticker:    ABT.andO;Topic:     Pharmaceutical IndustryRecords ManagementAutomationInformation Storage and RetrievalCase Study.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>